{
  "texts": [
    "There are two drawbacks for the Lamport one-time digital signature: The signature and key for the Lamport method is simply too large, about the thousands of bits.",
    "What's more, this approach has serious security limitations: each key can only be used to sign one message, so the Lamport method is used here as an example of",
    "a \"one-time signature\".",
    "There have been many subsequent optimizations for Lamport one-time digital signature.",
    "To address the inability to sign multiple messages with a single key, Ralph Merkle proposed a new DSS based on Merkle's tree (Merkle 1980)."
  ]
}